750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*f2jwV3DXJLLO5rCx-bPQRQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*f2jwV3DXJLLO5rCx-bPQRQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*f2jwV3DXJLLO5rCx-bPQRQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*f2jwV3DXJLLO5rCx-bPQRQ.png 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/max/700/1*f2jwV3DXJLLO5rCx-bPQRQ.png"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;"><strong>Image credit: Taken from google search, source was not mentioned. Let me know if it is your image and I can add the credit</strong></p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Encoder</strong> refers to the part of the network which reads the sentence to be translated, and, <strong>Decoder</strong> is the part of the network which translates the sentence into desired language.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7">Limitations of RNN</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Apart from all of its usefulness RNN does have certain limitations major of which are :</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><ol><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Examples of RNN architecture stated above are capable of capturing the dependencies in only one direction of language. Basically in case of Natural Language Processing it assumes that the word coming after has no effect on the meaning of the word coming before. With our experience of languages we know that it is certainly not true.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">RNN are also not very good in capturing long term dependencies and the problem of vanishing gradients resurface in RNN.</li></ol></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Both these limitations give rise to new types of RNN architectures which are being discussed below.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7">Gated Recurrent Unit</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">It is a modification in the basic recurrent unit which helps to capture long range dependencies and also help a lot in fixing vanishing gradient problem.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:79%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 584px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*xtEkE4BDySwNJ4FF2RlakA.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*xtEkE4BDySwNJ4FF2RlakA.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*xtEkE4BDySwNJ4FF2RlakA.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*xtEkE4BDySwNJ4FF2RlakA.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*xtEkE4BDySwNJ4FF2RlakA.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*xtEkE4BDySwNJ4FF2RlakA.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1168/format:webp/1*xtEkE4BDySwNJ4FF2RlakA.png 1168w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 584px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*xtEkE4BDySwNJ4FF2RlakA.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*xtEkE4BDySwNJ4FF2RlakA.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*xtEkE4BDySwNJ4FF2RlakA.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*xtEkE4BDySwNJ4FF2RlakA.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*xtEkE4BDySwNJ4FF2RlakA.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*xtEkE4BDySwNJ4FF2RlakA.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1168/1*xtEkE4BDySwNJ4FF2RlakA.png 1168w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/max/584/1*xtEkE4BDySwNJ4FF2RlakA.png"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;"><strong>Image credit: Taken from google search, source was not mentioned. Let me know if it is your image and I can add the credit</strong></p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content7 cid-ttbhFZC4Ql" id="content7-8" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
        <div class="container"><div class="row justify-content-center"><div class="col-12 col-md-9"><blockquote><p class="ff4">GRU consists of an additional memory unit commonly referred as an update gate or a reset gate. <strong>Apart from the usual neural unit with sigmoid function and softmax for output it contains an additional unit with tanh as an activation function</strong>. Tanh is used since its output can be both positive and negative hence can be used for both scaling up and down. The output from this unit is then combined with the activation input to update the value of the memory cell.</p></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Thus at each step value of both the hidden unit and the memory unit are updated. The value in the memory unit, plays a role in deciding the value of activation being passed on to the next unit.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">For a more detailed explanation one can refer to <a href="https://towardsdatascience.com/understanding-gru-networks-2ef37df6c9be" target="_self">https://towardsdatascience.com/understanding-gru-networks-2ef37df6c9be</a></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>LSTM</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">In LSTM architecture instead of having one update gate as in GRU there is an update gate and a forget gate.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:96%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*MpQK5P9Ihx2TEhRGvE-U4Q.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*MpQK5P9Ihx2TEhRGvE-U4Q.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*MpQK5P9Ihx2TEhRGvE-U4Q.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*MpQK5P9Ihx2TEhRGvE-U4Q.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*MpQK5P9Ihx2TEhRGvE-U4Q.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*MpQK5P9Ihx2TEhRGvE-U4Q.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*MpQK5P9Ihx2TEhRGvE-U4Q.png 1400w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*MpQK5P9Ihx2TEhRGvE-U4Q.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*MpQK5P9Ihx2TEhRGvE-U4Q.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*MpQK5P9Ihx2TEhRGvE-U4Q.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*MpQK5P9Ihx2TEhRGvE-U4Q.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*MpQK5P9Ihx2TEhRGvE-U4Q.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*MpQK5P9Ihx2TEhRGvE-U4Q.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*MpQK5P9Ihx2TEhRGvE-U4Q.png 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/max/700/1*MpQK5P9Ihx2TEhRGvE-U4Q.png"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;">Image credit: Andrew Ng deep learning Coursera</p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">This architecture gives the memory cell an option of keeping the old value at time t-1 and adding to it the value at time t.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">A more detailed explanation of LSTM is available at <a href="http://colah.github.io/posts/2015-08-Understanding-LSTMs/" target="_self">http://colah.github.io/posts/2015-08-Understanding-LSTMs/</a></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7">Bidirectional RNN</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">In the above RNN architectures effects of occurrences at only the previous time stamps can be taken into account. In the case of NLP it means that it takes into account the effects of the word written only before the current word . But this is not the case in a language structure and thus Bi-directional RNN come to the rescue.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:96%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*80HEc6uNib9RX1bE4YR2hA.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*80HEc6uNib9RX1bE4YR2hA.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*80HEc6uNib9RX1bE4YR2hA.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*80HEc6uNib9RX1bE4YR2hA.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*80HEc6uNib9RX1bE4YR2hA.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*80HEc6uNib9RX1bE4YR2hA.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*80HEc6uNib9RX1bE4YR2hA.png 1400w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*80HEc6uNib9RX1bE4YR2hA.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*80HEc6uNib9RX1bE4YR2hA.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*80HEc6uNib9RX1bE4YR2hA.png 